Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.48,0:01:35.24,Title Part 5,Sign,0,0,0,,{\fad(402,394)\pos(107,923)\fs60}Episodio 20  Final Order from the Boss
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.49,0:01:39.16,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,How long until we arrive?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.95,0:01:41.95,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,We're almost at the Rialto Bridge. {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rialto_Bridge}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.95,0:01:43.66,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,It will be another five minutes or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.66,0:01:45.71,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Good. Keep going.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.71,0:01:49.04,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Buccellati, can you remind me \Nwhat the boss's orders entailed?{Literally "What were the contents of the order from the boss?" but that's daft. -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.38,0:01:53.42,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I'll go over the boss's message again.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.97,0:01:58.76,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,{\an8}Listen closely. {I know this is insanely liberal but MEH -T}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.51,0:02:05.48,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,"The information contained on this disc was transferred to it \Nthe moment you all boarded the train in Naples.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.85,0:02:12.19,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,As such, I must inform you that I do not know\N if you are currently being pursued...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.19,0:02:16.36,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...nor how many of you have presently fallen.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.36,0:02:23.37,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,The information on this disc will assist you in safely \Nreuniting me with my daughter, which is my final order.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.37,0:02:31.71,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,But I warn you; should you deviate from the instructions \Ncontained on this disc even slightly, you will be shown no mercy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.21,0:02:38.30,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,If any of you do anything I have not instructed, \Nwhether accidentally or intentionally...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.30,0:02:42.43,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...I will interpret it as an act of hostility.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.85,0:02:44.64,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Now, here is my final order.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.23,0:02:49.48,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Those of you remaining will depart...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.10,0:02:52.23,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...for the island of San Giorgio Maggiore. {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/San_Giorgio_Maggiore}{I like how even Wikipedia mentions it being referenced in Jojo -T}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.23,0:02:57.15,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,You will accompany my daughter to the top \Nof the great bell tower at the local church.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.69,0:03:02.32,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Once my daughter has been safely escorted there,\N your mission will be completed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.70,0:03:05.74,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Order one: There are no stairs leading to the top of the tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.74,0:03:09.50,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Currently, the only means of reaching \Nthe top floor is through a single elevator.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.79,0:03:13.96,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Only Trish and one designated bodyguard \Nare permitted to use the elevator.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.96,0:03:20.68,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Order two: The bodyguard is prohibited from carrying any knives, guns, cell phones, or similar items.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.34,0:03:26.93,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,{\an8}Order three: You must reach the island \Nwithin fifteen minutes of successfully retrieving this disc.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.93,0:03:32.65,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,{\an8}Furthermore, the disc has been outfitted with a tracking device, \Nso I will know when you are on the move.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.15,0:03:37.82,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Order four: The rest of you will remain on the boat. \NYou are not allowed to step foot on the island."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.11,0:03:39.03,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,That's everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.61,0:03:42.91,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Buccellati, we've arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.03,0:03:48.58,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,So the boss is at the top of that tower right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.58,0:03:51.66,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,He must be incredibly cautious\N considering how detailed his orders were.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.29,0:03:56.17,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,Though I suppose if he weren't, \Nhe wouldn't be the boss of an organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.17,0:03:59.88,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Anyway, our mission is just about done now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.88,0:04:02.93,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,None of us died on the way, \Nso I guess it went well in the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.93,0:04:06.30,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Yeah, just barely, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.30,0:04:09.10,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,We should have some fun in Venice\N for a bit before we head home.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.10,0:04:10.60,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I hear they got great eats.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.60,0:04:12.48,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,The food's good here, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.48,0:04:15.44,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,I forgot how hungry I was!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.44,0:04:17.57,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,What do they got?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.57,0:04:20.57,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Squid ink pasta, horsehair crab salad...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.57,0:04:25.07,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,...and I hear Hotel Cipriani serves great carpaccio. {https://www.belmond.com/hotels/europe/italy/venice/belmond-hotel-cipriani/}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.07,0:04:26.20,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Hey, knock it off!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.53,0:04:28.28,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Don't let your guard down!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.28,0:04:30.20,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,This mission isn't over yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.58,0:04:32.71,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Narancia, keep an eye on the radar.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.71,0:04:34.25,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,G-Got it...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.54,0:04:36.04,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Buccellati...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.04,0:04:38.46,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,...I volunteer to be her bodyguard.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.92,0:04:42.92,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I'll escort her to the top of the bell tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.92,0:04:45.47,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Who the hell do you think you are?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.47,0:04:49.72,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,It's Buccellati's obligation as capo to escort her, idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.72,0:04:53.73,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,The boss didn't specify since\N he didn't know who would still be alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.65,0:04:58.98,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Of course. I'll go.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.52,0:05:00.61,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,All right, Trish.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.94,0:05:03.99,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,The two of us will enter the island as instructed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.29,0:05:14.71,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,I know...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.71,0:05:17.08,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,This is our chance to unmask the boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.08,0:05:18.71,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,I'll do whatever I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.29,0:05:24.92,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Oh yeah, Giorno. Could you give me that brooch of yours \Nas a good luck charm on this final mission?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.80,0:05:27.76,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Ladybugs are considered insects of the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.22,0:05:30.05,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,They're symbols of life, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.76,0:05:32.85,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,They make good luck charms, don't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.14,0:05:34.85,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Oh, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.85,0:05:37.94,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Yes. Ladybugs bring very good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.78,0:05:48.07,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,This brooch imbued with life by \NGold Experience's ability will act as a tracking device.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.70,0:05:49.66,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,Buccellati...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.53,0:05:52.20,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,What is it, Fugo?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.20,0:05:55.21,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,I would like to take this opportunity to say something.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.21,0:05:57.17,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Why so formal? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.75,0:06:04.88,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,I believed you would become capo someday,\N and I believe you'll be able to complete this mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.97,0:06:07.09,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Of course he can.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.47,0:06:12.72,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,Let's aim for an even higher position in the organization!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.39,0:06:16.73,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Yeah... We will.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.73,0:06:18.90,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Let's go, Trish.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.52,0:06:26.69,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,If I can somehow get this onto the boss's body...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.69,0:06:28.99,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,...Giorno will be able to track him down.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.62,0:06:33.33,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,For now, I need to figure out who he is...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.66,0:06:34.83,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,...at any cost.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.67,0:07:29.97,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,The elevator is open.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.38,0:07:34.43,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,It only has buttons for the first floor and roof.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.43,0:07:36.81,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,It goes directly to either. \NThere are no other floors to stop on.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.81,0:07:37.77,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,What's...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.10,0:07:41.44,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,...What's going to happen to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.65,0:07:47.69,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,I was suddenly kidnapped by gangsters like you guys, \Nwas threatened with my life...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.69,0:07:52.78,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,...and now, I'm about to be taken\Nto a father I've never loved or even met.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.78,0:07:56.74,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,What will happen to me after this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.87,0:08:02.46,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,The boss is just concerned for your safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.25,0:08:08.38,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,As for what will happen to you after this, \NI have a good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.38,0:08:10.42,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,First, you'll be given a different name.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.30,0:08:13.76,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,You may even need plastic surgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.76,0:08:15.89,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,You'll be given new ID and a new family registry...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.64,0:08:22.10,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...and be sent to some faraway country \Nwhere you'll live a happy life. {"faraway foreign" is redundant -G}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.77,0:08:26.15,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Your father has the power to make that happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.07,0:08:29.78,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Here. Let me give you a hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.53,0:08:36.82,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,It's not as if... {I HATE TIMING LINES LIKE THIS AAAAAH -Gyro}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.49,0:08:40.83,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,...I-I'm nervous or anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.15,0:09:08.98,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,I wonder...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.90,0:09:12.44,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,...if I'll come to like my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.28,0:09:17.07,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,No family ever worries about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.49,0:09:22.08,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.08,0:09:23.37,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.83,0:09:27.71,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,To even worry about it is odd...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.29,0:09:30.92,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,We're almost at the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.76,0:09:39.47,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Trish? Tri{\fscx300}-{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.65,0:09:51.52,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Wh-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.73,0:09:55.90,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Trish... No... What's...?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.03,0:10:00.33,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,Trish and I should be the only ones here...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.33,0:10:04.41,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,No one other than the members of my team know I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.41,0:10:06.41,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,No... It couldn't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.41,0:10:08.33,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,Could the boss...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.33,0:10:10.88,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,...in order to ensure he remains hidden...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.88,0:10:13.84,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Did he give us this escort mission...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.38,0:10:20.22,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...so that he could personally eliminate his own daughter?!
Comment: 0,0:10:23.10,0:10:23.14,Main,,0,0,0,,B
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.48,0:10:34.32,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,Bruno Buccellati was born the son of \Na fisherman in a suburb of Naples.{HOLY MOOD WHIPLASH, BATMAN. -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.73,0:10:37.45,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,His father was never much of a people person...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.45,0:10:44.04,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,...but he was an earnest and honest fisherman \Nwho tried to protect his family from the cruelties of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.95,0:10:47.00,Flashback,Bruno's Dad,0,0,0,,Bruno.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.00,0:10:47.91,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.58,0:10:50.38,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,You need me to fix the net?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.38,0:10:51.29,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.42,0:10:59.47,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,His mother was a kind woman, \Nand Buccellati loved the conversations he had with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.80,0:11:03.72,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,He eagerly looked forward to the\N bedtime stories she read him before he slept.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.72,0:11:05.97,Flashback,Bruno's Mom,0,0,0,,All right, it's time to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.97,0:11:07.02,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.98,0:11:10.65,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,Something happened when Buccellati was seven years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.65,0:11:13.06,Flashback,Bruno's Dad,0,0,0,,So what are you going to do about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.06,0:11:18.15,Flashback,Bruno's Mom,0,0,0,,Well... I'm looking for change, \Nso I want to leave this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.03,0:11:22.37,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,After ten years of marriage, \Nhis parents divorced.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.95,0:11:28.08,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,As for why, only his parents could tell you that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.41,0:11:31.54,Flashback,Bruno's Dad,0,0,0,,What are we going to do about Bruno?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.25,0:11:37.92,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,After talking it out among themselves, \NBuccellati's parents decided to let him decide.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.88,0:11:43.72,Flashback,Bruno's Mom,0,0,0,,Bruno, your father and I both love you very much...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.72,0:11:45.72,Flashback,Bruno's Mom,0,0,0,,...but we're going to be living apart from now on.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.26,0:11:50.18,Flashback,Bruno's Mom,0,0,0,,Who would you like to live with? \NMe or your father?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.18,0:11:52.15,Flashback,Bruno's Mom,0,0,0,,We'd like you to decide.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.19,0:11:57.40,Flashback,Bruno's Mom,0,0,0,,You want to leave this place \Nand go to the city with me, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.40,0:11:59.53,Flashback,Bruno's Mom,0,0,0,,You're a smart boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.53,0:12:01.61,Flashback,Bruno's Mom,0,0,0,,You'd like to go to a good school, wouldn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.16,0:12:05.07,Flashback,Bruno's Mom,0,0,0,,You'll meet so many more children your age there!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.07,0:12:07.33,Flashback,Bruno's Mom,0,0,0,,So you'll come live with me, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.33,0:12:09.08,Flashback,Bruno's Mom,0,0,0,,Won't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.04,0:12:11.12,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.87,0:12:13.79,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,...want to live with Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.59,0:12:19.38,Flashback,Bruno's Mom,0,0,0,,What?! \NBruno, you should really think about this!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.38,0:12:20.92,Flashback,Bruno's Mom,0,0,0,,You like me better, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.76,0:12:24.30,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,I'm staying here with Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.30,0:12:25.72,Flashback,Bruno's Mom,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.39,0:12:29.27,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,Mom is strong...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.27,0:12:31.35,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,She should be able to make it anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.35,0:12:32.35,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.61,0:12:39.11,Flashback,Bruno's Mom,0,0,0,,All right, I'm leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.78,0:12:44.03,Flashback,Bruno's Mom,0,0,0,,I'll come back once a month to visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.03,0:12:44.82,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.58,0:12:59.17,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,As Buccellati's gut feeling at the time warned him, \Nhis mother remarried to a man from Milan two years after leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.17,0:13:03.22,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,From then on, \Nhe only ever saw his mother at Christmas time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.22,0:13:10.81,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,His father, determined after his wife left him for the city, \Ndid his best to send Buccellati to a good school.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.81,0:13:14.19,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,Dad, I think we'll get some customers soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.89,0:13:17.02,Flashback,Bruno's Dad,0,0,0,,Oh, I guess it's about that time...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.36,0:13:19.94,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,I'll reapply the nets.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.94,0:13:22.36,Flashback,Bruno's Dad,0,0,0,,All right. I'll let you handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.11,0:13:27.57,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,Though he had been nothing more than a fisherman until this point, \Nin order to earn money for his son's tuition...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.57,0:13:33.33,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,...he began taking tourists and other fishermen on his boat whenever he had time to spare.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.33,0:13:37.58,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,And the wheel of fate continued to turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.50,0:13:41.84,Flashback,Bruno's Dad,0,0,0,,Sirs, that island isn't good for fishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.84,0:13:43.51,Flashback,Bruno's Dad,0,0,0,,There are better{\fscx300}-{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.21,0:13:43.51,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,Whatever!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.51,0:13:46.01,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,That's where we wanna go fishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.01,0:13:48.51,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,So just shut up and take us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.51,0:13:49.72,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,We clear?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.60,0:13:53.43,Flashback,Bruno's Dad,0,0,0,,R-Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.23,0:14:01.02,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,That evening, Buccellati's father was rescued by the Coast Guard, \Nhis body riddled with bullet holes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.02,0:14:04.19,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,He's sustained seven bullet wounds to his arms, \Nshoulders, chest, and torso.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.19,0:14:05.82,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,Not all of the bullets passed through.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.11,0:14:03.36,Flashback,Nurse,0,0,0,,{\an8}We need an operating room open!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.36,0:14:05.82,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,{\an8}Dad! Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.82,0:14:08.07,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.62,0:14:14.87,Flashback,Nurse,0,0,0,,For now, please just wait until his surgery is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.87,0:14:18.83,Flashback,Nurse,0,0,0,,Be strong. \NDo you have contact information for anyone else in your family?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.83,0:14:19.92,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.88,0:14:27.80,Flashback,Cop,0,0,0,,Forensics is dropping by later, \Nso give them this as evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.80,0:14:28.76,Flashback,Nurse,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.76,0:14:29.59,Flashback,Cop,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.59,0:14:30.35,Flashback,Nurse,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.35,0:14:33.81,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,H-How did this happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.81,0:14:36.68,Flashback,Cop,0,0,0,,Evening, son.\N Is he your father?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.68,0:14:38.81,Flashback,Cop,0,0,0,,We found this at the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.44,0:14:43.57,Flashback,Cop,0,0,0,,Apparently, your father witnessed a drug deal going down.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.57,0:14:45.65,Flashback,Cop,0,0,0,,They shot him up so he wouldn't speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.07,0:14:49.28,Flashback,Cop,0,0,0,,Your father is an important witness in this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.28,0:14:53.20,Flashback,Cop,0,0,0,,We'd rather he not die, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.20,0:14:54.83,Flashback,Cop,0,0,0,,{\an8}I'm sure he'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.20,0:14:56.62,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,Dad was shot because of something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.79,0:15:03.55,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,Luckily, Buccellati's father survived.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.92,0:15:08.26,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,Despite being shot seven times, \Nnone of the wounds were fatal...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.63,0:15:12.85,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,...and the boat that found and rescued him\N happened to have supplies to treat his wounds...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.85,0:15:15.31,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,...which allowed him to survive \Nuntil he reached the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.31,0:15:17.73,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,He was graced by good luck all around.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.73,0:15:25.11,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,But in terms of Buccellati's life, \Nit may have been better if he had died.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.11,0:15:33.28,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,There are certain difficult situations\N where an opportunity to follow the right path isn't presented.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.16,0:15:42.00,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,Fishermen are way too damn tough, shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.00,0:15:44.46,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,I'll keep watch! \NJust hurry and finish him!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.46,0:15:47.38,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,You got a lot of nerve \Nmaking us come out here at night...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.38,0:15:50.05,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,Now go to hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.84,0:15:55.14,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,Wh-Who the fuck are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.14,0:15:58.14,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,A k-kid? H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.14,0:16:00.02,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,{\an8}What were you doing under the bed?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.02,0:16:02.10,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,{\an8}Th-That knife's dangerous! \NPut it down!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.23,0:16:02.10,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,It's just a fucking kid! \NGrab the knife!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.61,0:16:09.99,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,Wh-What are you{\fscx300}-{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.41,0:16:23.71,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,I'll protect you, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.08,0:16:28.25,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,Don't worry. \NTake your time getting better.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.25,0:16:35.68,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,At the age of twelve, Bruno Buccellati committed murder \Nand entered a world no one should ever set foot in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.10,0:16:38.31,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,I can't turn back now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.31,0:16:41.31,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,They'll keep trying to get revenge and shut us up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.31,0:16:43.14,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,I can't trust the police, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.02,0:16:49.65,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,The only protection afforded to him and his father was \Nan organization that controlled the city from the shadows.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.98,0:16:52.57,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,Buccellati knocked on the doors of that organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.32,0:16:57.16,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,And in return for his service and undying loyalty...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.16,0:16:59.62,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,...they guaranteed his family's safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.62,0:17:04.33,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,Believing the organization to be the true form of justice, he worked hard there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.33,0:17:09.50,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,He made a name for himself within the organization, \Nbefore the capo Polpo eventually took a liking to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.80,0:17:14.51,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,Five years later, Buccellati's father died \Ndue to complications from his wounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.01,0:17:19.93,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,Buccellati loathed the white powder of greed \Nthat had dragged him and his father into this situation...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.93,0:17:22.06,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,...and swore that he would never forgive it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.60,0:17:23.48,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.94,0:17:27.77,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,I-I'm sorry!\N I won't bother them again!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.77,0:17:29.52,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,I'll forget about that family!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.52,0:17:33.78,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,Good. \NNot like you'll be able to regret it once you're dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.78,0:17:35.53,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,If you're also a gangster{\fscx300}-{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.20,0:17:39.58,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,Those are...!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.58,0:17:41.70,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,Hey! \NWhat the hell is that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.54,0:17:49.00,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,He learned that the organization's boss, a man whom he thought \Nembodied justice, was involved in dealing the drugs he despised.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.46,0:17:51.88,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,In this city?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.88,0:17:54.13,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,I thought they were forbidden!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.64,0:18:02.27,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,And now...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.27,0:18:03.64,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Now the boss is...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.14,0:18:06.23,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,The most heinous form of evil...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.56,0:18:13.07,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...is to knowingly exploit the innocent for personal gain!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.07,0:18:16.24,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,A father did this to his innocent daughter...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.24,0:18:18.07,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...all to cover his own ass?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.41,0:18:19.70,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Unforgivable!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.70,0:18:23.95,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Twice now you've betrayed my heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.25,0:18:33.05,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,There! \NTrish is still alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.60,0:18:42.31,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,All right. It held.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.31,0:18:45.27,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,But damn, I can't see his face.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.56,0:18:50.69,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Boss, my original plan was just to uncover your identity,\N but things have changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.69,0:18:53.53,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I'm going to eliminate you here and now!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.53,0:18:54.53,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I don't have time...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.82,0:18:57.78,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...but the boss won't be \Nexpecting me to betray him so suddenly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.15,0:18:58.82,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,This will be...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.74,0:19:01.87,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...an assassination.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.79,0:19:08.33,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,I'll get ahead of the boss on \Nhis escape route and finish him there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.59,0:19:22.55,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,This...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.14,0:19:24.76,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,This hole...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.47,0:19:26.68,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.68,0:19:30.27,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,It's the stairway to the charnel house \Nlike you'd find in the basement of any church.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.60,0:19:35.02,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,Once he's eliminated Trish down there\N and thinks he's in the clear...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.02,0:19:38.03,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,...he'll make his escape \Nthrough the other side of the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.79,0:19:52.83,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,I managed to get here first.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.21,0:19:58.26,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,Here he comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.32,0:20:19.44,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,He came down the stairs!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.07,0:20:20.74,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.74,0:20:23.36,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,You would be wise to leave this place...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.36,0:20:24.66,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,...Bruno Buccellati.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.74,0:20:27.99,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,If you step out from behind that pillar...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.99,0:20:30.21,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,...you will die.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.42,0:20:38.88,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Sticky Fingers!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.76,0:20:45.47,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I-It's going to break off!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.73,0:20:59.61,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,So he knew I was after him...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.61,0:21:03.36,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,But since he hid himself again...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.36,0:21:05.99,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...I can only assume he isn't very powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.99,0:21:08.28,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I'd like to know your motive here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.91,0:21:13.08,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,What is the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.08,0:21:17.88,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I've had the utmost respect \Nfor your work on this mission thus far.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.50,0:21:21.71,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,{\pos(850,1055)}Did the joy of becoming a capo\N not satiate your greed?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.09,0:21:28.35,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,{\pos(850,1055)}Or has your hubris fooled you into believing you could get the better of me?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.01,0:21:31.31,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,When Trish wakes up...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.93,0:21:34.94,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...I'm going to tell her \Nthat she never had a father.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.94,0:21:36.27,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Trish?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.90,0:21:39.11,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,What about Trish?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.11,0:21:42.03,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,My daughter has nothing to do with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.03,0:21:45.99,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,You'll never understand \Nwhat I feel within my heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.62,0:21:50.45,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Giorno?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.45,0:21:51.66,Narrator,Giorno,0,0,0,,Buccellati!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.66,0:21:54.62,Narrator,Giorno,0,0,0,,Yes, I know he's on the move.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.62,0:21:58.29,Narrator,Giorno,0,0,0,,{\pos(1310,1055)}I know exactly where the brooch\Nyou put on the boss's body is.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.29,0:22:00.80,Narrator,Giorno,0,0,0,,{\pos(1310,1055)}Right now, he's at the bottom of the stairs\N leading to the charnel house.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.80,0:22:04.17,Narrator,Giorno,0,0,0,,He's right near the pillar that's \Nabout two meters away from the stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.17,0:22:05.76,Narrator,Giorno,0,0,0,,But wait, Buccellati!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.01,0:22:09.05,Narrator,Giorno,0,0,0,,Something tells me... you're in trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.76,0:22:12.39,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,There you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.81,0:22:17.44,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Take this! \NSticky Fingers!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.61,0:22:27.86,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,The one who was in the pillar's shadow...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.32,0:22:29.37,Thoughts,Bruno,0,0,0,,...was me!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.70,0:22:36.04,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Wh-What...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.87,0:22:37.71,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,What's going o{\fscx300}-{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.71,0:22:41.75,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,I've shown you this... as a parting gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.38,0:22:45.22,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Since this is the end,\N I'll enlighten you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.22,0:22:51.72,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,What you just saw and felt \Nwas yourself from the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.39,0:22:56.39,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,{\pos(1240,1055)}You from several seconds in the past\N just witnessed your future self.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.73,0:23:01.11,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,That is my King Crimson's ability. {Because of this line, I'm going to edit the rest as if it's Diavolo talking, not his Stand. -T}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.11,0:23:03.94,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,It erased time, then leapt past it.
